Estee Lauder Drops After 2012 Profit Forecast Misses Estimates

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-08-15T21:35:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/estee-lauder-drops-after-2012-profit-forecast-misses-estimates.html
Estee Lauder Cos. slumped today,
declining the most in the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index, after the
maker of Clinique and Bobbi Brown makeup lines forecast profit
in 2012 will be below the average analyst estimate.  The New York-based company said in a statement today
adjusted earnings next year will at least $4 a share and no more
than $4.20, falling short of the $4.35 median prediction by
analysts in a Bloomberg survey. Chief Executive Officer Fabrizio Freda said on a conference call with investors he expects a
“much tougher” competitive environment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inyoung Hwang in  New York  at 
